editorialNotes.standard: We secretly dream of winning the lottery and equipping our living room with six TVs so we never miss a game. Until that day comes—which, okay, it probably won’t—Sportsnet’s fantastically in-depth offerings keep us on top of every touchdown, home run, and GOOOOOOOAL. That's why it's our 2016 App of the Year for Apple TV.

Its minimal interface stays out of our way so we can focus on draft picks, trades, and managing our lineup. But the best part? ESPN’s got mini-stories on all of the hot prospects. editorialNotes.standard: The ultimate app for any football fan, NFL Mobile offers an insanely robust experience from the preseason to the playoffs. A smartly designed interface puts the spotlight on colorful photos and videos, and breaking news is easy to navigate and share. The astoundingly long list of features includes drive charts, real-time scores, and live stat trackers. Plus, on-demand games, access to preseason games, and more all become available with purchase of the NFL Game Pass 2016 Subscription, so there’s always something new to watch, analyze, and read.
